	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101156199516870><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6019&mid=101156199516870>Yup</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6019&mid=101156199516870#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=131846><span id= >Syfiari</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>15 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 20th 5:27 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Anonymous (the one above Rhyoss), please do your best to be quiet and know about the subject you're trying to talk about before correcting someone.&nbsp;&nbsp;Haste does NOT reduce the delay of a weapon... that's an assumption that's been plaguing the EQ mindset for years now.  It increases the number of attacks you get in a given amount of time... which would *seem* like the same thing as delay reduction, but it isn't.<br><br>As for the Sporali Gloves... if I was some low-mid level individual and/or didn't have the money to twink an alt with an FBSS/SCH or better, these would be just fine.  An effectively 10% increase in damage dealt is better than none, even at the sacrifice of some AC in your Hands slot and a couple *very* minor resist reductions.  By the time resists even matter (in the high 40's), you're more than high enough to get into an FBSS camp.<br>&nbsp;<br>".. call me 'pansy elf wench' one more time."<br><br>/em draws an arrow...</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
