	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>Hehe I posted above the MOFO post. He didn't mean me, he means the guy above me. Honest. :)<br><br>Hehe WRONG Mr. Wish-We-Were-Smarter.<br>You don't subtract the haste percentage from the delay, you add it to your speed; there's a big difference. <br><br>With a 50% haste item, your delay is not halved to 50%, you don't swing twice as fast. Instead, your speed is increased to 150% of base, so your delay is 2/3 of the original value, and you get 3 swings in the time you'd normally get 2 without haste. It takes 100% haste to double your speed, not 50%.<br><br>I know, this makes the arithmetic a little tougher...say 5th grade instead of 3rd grade. So we'll give you a couple years to figure it out.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
