	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your logic is flawed.&nbsp;&nbsp;The haste percentage doesn't reduce the delay by that amount.  Rather, it increases the damage over time by that amount by adjusting the delay.  Not quite the same thing.<br><br>1 / (1/delay * (1 + Haste))<br><br>1/50 * 1.10 = 0.22<br>1/0.22 = 45.45 (which in this case rounds to 45)<br><br>However, if the haste was 100% (doing twice as much damage over time), the delay would be 25, *not* 0.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
