	   <tr><td colspan=2>ok... everytime I read the "how to figure out haste" crap I get more and more confused... but I did grasp it loosly.&nbsp;&nbsp;So for everyone who's still a little confused i'll explain how I figure it out.<br>Ok as the first guy said, he thought the haste on the gloves was 5% and in essence, it is.  And the second guy said it was 11% which in actuality it is.  Confused yet?<br>Ok VI decided that, if you get 100% haste and you attacked nonstop... that'd be a bit imbalancing =). SO!  VI decided to make the haste only work on half the weaon delay.  IE if you have a weapon with delay of 40 and the haste on your item is 10% then cut the delay in half 40 divided by 2 is 20 and then the haste percent 10% of 20 is 2... and then subtract that number from the delay 40 - 2 = 38.  so the new delay is 38 .. tah dah... if i'm wrong.  Oh well.  If i'm right, yipee.  don't flame me too much if i'm super wrong, my poor ego couldn't handle it. =)<br>&nbsp;<br>Jawnimus Dreadbeard (formerly Gonecornholin /rude GM's)<br>55 Revenant (Karana Server)<br>"Your greed is the blade against your throat, begin the cleansing."</td></tr>
